FBIS4-53704 "dreas099_d_94001" FBIS-EAS-94-099 Daily Report 20 May 1994 South Korea Radio Reports U.S. To Resume Talks With DPRK Radio Reports U.S. To Resume Talks With DPRK SK2005233194 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 2200 GMT 20 May 94 SK2005233194 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network Korean BFN [By Mun Chae-cho from Washington] [Text] It has been learned that in a meeting of the U.S. National Security Council held early this morning at the White House, the United States has decided to hold a third round of high- level talks with North Korea as soon as possible. In today's meeting, the United States has reportedly discussed the resumption of the third round of U.S.-North Korean high-level talks in Geneva next month, at the earliest, as a result of the International Atomic Energy Agency's report that North Korea is cooperating on the nuclear inspections.
